messages.content: ComfyUI-CSV-Loader is a custom node for ComfyUI that allows access to positive and negative prompts associated with a name from CSV files for prompt building within the ComfyUI interface.

To install ComfyUI-CSV-Loader, unzip the ComfyUI-CSV-Loader.zip file and place it into the custom_nodes folder within your ComfyUI installation without changing the naming to keep the mapping for the CSV files consistent.
Where are the CSV files located in ComfyUI-CSV-Loader?
The CSV files are located in the ComfyUI\custom_nodes\ComfyUI-CSV_Loader\CSV folder.
What CSV files are included in ComfyUI-CSV-Loader?
The CSV files included in ComfyUI-CSV-Loader are artists.csv, artmovements.csv, characters.csv, composition.csv, lighting.csv, negative.csv, positive.csv, settings.csv, and styles.csv.
Can the preloaded selections in the CSV files of ComfyUI-CSV-Loader be updated?
Yes, the preloaded selections in the CSV files of ComfyUI-CSV-Loader can always be updated.
Is there a workflow available for testing ComfyUI-CSV-Loader?
Yes, there is a workflow available at https://comfyworkflows.com/?workflow_id=320ac429-28cd-4192-a7c3-da1ed3fd1893 for testing ComfyUI-CSV-Loader.
Who is the developer of ComfyUI-CSV-Loader?
The developer of ComfyUI-CSV-Loader is PCMonsterx, and the repository can be found at https://github.com/PCMonsterx/ComfyUI-CSV-Loader.
